comment:
Interesting game with lovely components and a theme which makes the rules intuitive.

My only complaint is that the scoring condition creates a thematic disconnect. Because you get no points for presence on the board, and the game ends at a predictable point, the winner is usually the person without any trees at the end. The game would be more satisfying if the winner could gaze at their lovingly cultivated garden.
